    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 24:10-13",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 24:10-13",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou shalt not go in — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To prevent both the poor man’s reproach, by having his wants exposed, and the creditor’s greediness, which might be occasioned by the sight of something which he desired, and the debtor could not spare. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The pledge ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— He shall choose what pledge he pleases, provided it be sufficient for the purpose. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou shalt not sleep — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But restore it before night, which intimates that he should take no such thing for pledge without which a man could not sleep. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Bless thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bring down the blessing of God upon thee by his prayers: for though his prayers, if he be not a good man, shall not avail for his own behalf, yet they shall avail for thy benefit. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "It shall be righteousness unto thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Esteemed and accepted by God as a work of righteousness, or mercy.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
